Source:  Te Waimate
Author:  STUDHOLME
Vol / Page:  36
Edition:
Quote:  The Maori crossed deep rivers like the Waitaki on mokihis (rafts) which were skilfully constructed of bundles of bundles of dry raupo or korari (flax) sticks.
